annotation.TEXT: Oh, hold on. I might be able to get my motor back.
Only three Yoshi coins, and the game gave me a Fire Flower there. Also... Argh, I've gotta remember to try bringing that extra P-switch all the way here in a future episode.
Oh, yeah. This cutscene.
Now, I didn't mention this last time due to the WMM hiccup, but I assume these green blocks won't let you pass if you didn't get enough coins (mainly from eating dolphins).
Ack! Well, whatever. There's power up filter stripes here anyway, so that hit's irrelevant.
Just like the Easy version, there's nothing of interest to the right here. Also, the HP system is forcing me to be fiery this time.
Push! Sound channels enabled again.
Whoa, okay, Pokey heads are flammable/inflammable. (They're actually footballs.)
Eek, that thing was practically on my butt for a second there!
Oh, not this again. I'll just cape spin through these right away.
Pfft. I don't know what I was thinking there.
Cirno: "That was my DUMMY! I got you like a hawk catches its prey, halfwit! The real boss is me, the strongest, and I'll show you just why I am! Get outta my FACE!"
Oh, pudding... Okay, so this is the "Here We Go!" vanilla SMW music, but with sound channels 1, 2, 3, 4, and 6 disabled. Umm, yeah. There's still a channel playing music.
Alright, it's boss time!
HARD
Aw, Yoshi's not allowed in that pipe. Bye, Yoshi!
BTW, someone asked if I could glitch myself into the layer 2 ceiling by entering this pipe here at the right time, and I tried that off-camera, and you die while IN the pipe.
Ooh, nice. I managed to cape-thwack the Goomba straight into her despite the spikes there.

And so Cirno's castle was conquered. Cirno: "I lost at my strongest..." You've now beaten all the Normal stages. Congratulations! You think you're pretty good by now, right? Well, Marisa's challenging you to the Hard stages now. So you'd better get better...
Uhh... Yeah, this is what the SMW boss theme sounds like with sound channels 1, 2, 3, 4, and 6 disabled.
And Yoshi's head became a Lava Guy (Podoboo) for a moment there. I wonder if Yoshi was even meant to be allowed in this room at all.
Ah, in addition to the lack of platforms, there's now spikes added to this room on the Normal difficulty.
I think I'd like a better solution than just simply disabling sound channels, because as you can hear, it's not a perfect workaround.
Okay, I'll drop off the left side of that block if that's what you want, game.
Oh, yeah. I do want to either cape-thwack or get frozen by these things quickly, so that they aren't around to potentially freeze me while Cirno's launching other attacks at me.
D'oh! I ascended higher than I intended to there.
Okay, I've simply rewound back to the beginning of this room. Let's try this again and see if that pipe behaves this time.
As such, I didn't put in replacement music here. At least this is sufficient to avoid a copyright claim, but I'm not sure that I like this... Also, this disco shell is annoying me!
Yep, it's possible to cape-thwack an enemy without it destroying a weapon you're holding.
Zwee! Okay, here come the Bowser statue lasers. BTW, the red ones are faster than the blue ones, which was true in the Easy version of this level as well.
Aw, darn shrinker stripes... Huh, that Chuck ran over that lava pit. There must be enemy-only solid tiles just above it.
Does is erroneously think I'm on Yoshi for some reason? Well, it's messed up then, since it clearly made me dismount my trusty steed a couple of rooms ago.
...Um, what? ...Game, what's going on? Why am I not allowed to enter this pipe?
Close call there.
And that's that! Normal path complete!
And unfortunately, I can't go anywhere else here. I'm stuck in this tiny chamber.
D'oh. Didn't quite hit her with the Goomba right away that time, and now I've gotta wait for it to wake up.
Okay, here's the dolphin-eating room. BTW, the autoscroll here isn't tied to killing the Chuck or revealing Yoshi. It just automatically starts after a few seconds pass.
Yep, remember this map from back when I reached the Yellow Switch Palace? Well, let's take a look at it again.
Yep, there it goes. Hmm... I probably should've used this P-switch to get three coins towards my quota.
So next time, I begin the Hard levels. To be continued... Ze!
D'oh! Well, there goes my shell, shielding me from Torpedo Ted, just like that brave ice block earlier. Your death will not be in vain, shell!
Ah, so these munchers do indeed act like normal munchers. It's just that they use different graphics, and don't change to look like coins when a silver P-switch is hit.
That was a dumb hit, but the HP system is in effect, so it'll take two more hits to kill me.
Unlike Ninja Boy, I often like having a Fire Flower available to use, and fireballs are generally quite useful underwater, depending on what enemies you encounter.
Hakurei Shrine (Hard)
The layer 1 ceiling just above me is one tile lower than on Easy, so I have a bit less room to work with.
Whoa, I almost destroyed that Goomba with my spin jump. I should really only use normal jumps around it.
Oh, there are solid enemy-only tiles here.
Back to the castle setting, which I can effectively replace the music of, since the vanilla SMW castle music doesn't do what "Here We Go!" did.
Whoa, hello! I just collected an upside-down muncher!
So, we've gotta do the dolphin-eating part again, and with an increased quota. However, on the Easy path, I ate over 50 dolphins, so how hard could 25 be here?
D'oh! How'd I manage to screw that up? And I was duck-jumping that time too. Well, whatever. Does the pipe work this time?
Whoa, I'm surprised that I dodged the Rotisserie-Chicken-Disc there.
Anyway, this fight is just like the Easy version, except the floor is lower, and there are pits I could fall into.
Umm... I have no idea why the autoscroll suddenly started up again when the P-switch ended there... Well, whatever. I got outta there before I got crushed.
Aw, nuts. I was hoping that I could shell-kill that regular Lava Lotus. (I'm actually not sure whether they're even shell-killable in SMB3, to be honest.)
Cape feather? Oh, the HP system isn't in effect this time. Also, I'm just gonna go straight to ludicrous speed for the parts where I just sit on the turbo-cape button.
And with that, the warp star leading to the HARD WORLD„Å∏ appears!
This took quite a bit of time and effort to put together in WMM, though. Hmm... I wonder if there's a moon above the screen here in the Normal version of this level...
Well, I guess I'll have to invoke my space-time powers to get outta this jam.
Umm... Yep, and there was something up there that insta-killed me as well (probably lava).
Alright, this is so slow and boring that I'm going to double the speed of the footage for most of this room. (And I've made absolutely sure WMM didn't hiccup this time!)
Meh. Honestly, it doesn't matter whether I cape-thwack those or get frozen by them (except cape-thwacking them gets me a couple hundred points).
Oh, looks like the game's providing me with another swimming aid up ahead. I might absolutely need the speed, or maybe I'll just need it for a puzzle.
Huh, the game forced a mushroom onto me as I entered that pipe.
Whoa, that was close.
Hello!
I almost waited too long to mount Yoshi there. That would've sucked if I'd missed him.
At least I was given a replacement feather here. Ah, and as you can hear, the sound effects are playing while the vanilla SMW castle music isn't. Very nice.
Alright! Oh, and for some reason, Cirno does not add yet another spike to the room after the 4th hit.
Yeah, nuts to that, since I could just cape-thwack that block. I don't know why the shell didn't want to make that one block spin...
Okay, the dolphin generator stopped, so we must be nearing the end of the room.
Some of these Jelectros are on layer 2.
Whoa, that would've sucked if I let that Lava Guy hit me.
These attacks are the same as on Easy. In fact, I'd say that Cirno is totally identical regardless of difficulty, and it's just the arena and the HP system that changed.
Had to do a bit of dodging there this time, since I had to wait for the layer 2 walls to get out of my way.
Cirno: "You weren't half bad about getting THIS far... But can you make it to I, the strongest?" Get 5 coins in this room and have Yoshi eat 25 dolphins.
Sound channels enabled again, since we're back to the Cirno music.
Not even gonna bother trying to use the shell on these blocks.
And here come the random "Feeries", as I believe Zeldara109 called them. ("Fairies"+"Eeries".)
Alright, let's start eating dolphins like usual, and watch out for Boss Bass, like usual.
I'd better be careful of the dolphins here, of course, since they don't particularly care for my well-being.
Ha! The shrinker stripes didn't take away my reserve feather!
I see those layer 2 smashing munchers.
Whoa, bullets! Also, I probably should've duck-jumped onto these chains...
Looks like I'll need it purely for speed this time.
I guess the game still checks for your collision with layer 2 objects while you're in one of those SMB3-style pipes, and can declare you crush-killed before you emerge.
Oh, you are evil, game. Fortunately, I managed to avoid getting zapped by your trick.
To Hard World
And the HP system is gone again, giving me back my capes.
They're only dangerous after they've become one with the floor. So, those epic dodges last time weren't actually all that epic. Oh, well.
KA-BOOM!!!
Narrowly avoided those. The extra spikes in the Normal version arena make dodging those extra tricky.
There we go. BTW, remember those near-misses I had against this move last time? Well, turns out these spikes can't actually hurt you when they're initially tossed.
Whoops. Well, so much for my ice block. At least it protected me from a Torpedo Ted.
Alright, time for the real boss battle against Cirno herself!
28 coins from that block. I could've gotten 32 if I had done it perfectly, or 9001 if I had set up a block factory.
Oh, I just noticed that the HP system is in effect, since it says "HP 3" up there.
Space-time rewind count: 11
Yay, cape!
Moon count: 16 Demo count: 15
Outta my way, HB platform! Ooh, free flower.
Also, unlike the Easy level, there's no platforms in midair for me to stand on to stay safe from Boss Bass. I guess that makes sense.
Oh, yeah. If there's a layer 2 present, standing up in a 1-tile high passage while super works differently, and weirdly.
Alright, we're at the Okkusenman chambers now. First, the ON/OFF switch room with the spike ceiling on layer 2.
Well, that was rude... Maybe I should start all future levels by pausing the game, so I can see rude openings like that and avoid them on my first try.
Alright, here's the underwater portion, and I'll try not to lose the ice block to a hungry lotus this time.
Maybe if someone could take this hack (link's in description) and remove all of the vanilla SMW music from it somehow...
I'm pretty sure I've hit the quota by now, but I'll keep eating anyway.
I wonder why that block turned into a coin when I hit it? Is there a permanent P-switch effect going on in this room or something?
Yep, I wasn't about to fall for that again.
And yes, I've manually redone the annotations for this video.
Yeah, it's the butchered "Here We Go!" theme again. Well, there's the last two Yoshi coins. Also, hi, Yoshi!
Yoshi definitely helps a lot here!
At least Yoshi can stand on the spikes, just like with the munchers. And, they should be high enough to keep me safe from Boss Bass.
Alright, this round is done, but of course there's one more round...
A bit of loading here. I didn't cut this one out because it would've messed with the music.
So, we're at this "RUN, RUN, RUN!!!" part again.
Be careful of the higher spikes here. Yoshi only protects me from spikes and munchers that are directly below me. If I hit their sides or bottoms, I get hurt.
Yep, that blue spike went right through me harmlessly. Oh, and it seems Cirno always places those spikes in those spots after the 2nd and 3rd hits.
Okay, it works this time! Why didn't it work the previous time? I'm totally confuzzled on that one.
I can use this P-switch glitch to make fish and then eat those, I suppose. But anyway, I wonder what this extra P-switch is really meant for...
Alright!
Pfft. That was an unintentional block clone. Okay, come on, hit that other block already!
Hey there, Hot Foot. How's it going?
Hello, and welcome back to Scarlet Devil Mario! Now, TurnipEvernoteVirato said that I could disable some sound channels to mute the vanilla music but keep the SFX.
Okay, then. That was evil, but at least I got a moon out of it, which I won't have to worry about collecting again.
Oh, what? Oh, that Rotational-Symmetry-Disc's hub is apparently electrified.
Oh, nice! Another shell!
Finally got rid of the thing! I don't know why that gave me such a hard time. Anyway, moving on...
Wow, that was almost dangerous, the way I handled those ice blocks. Of course, I'm going to bring an ice block with me.
Jammed coin count: 1 Yoshi's tongue can reach it, though!
